---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import AuthorBio from "../components/AuthorBio.astro";
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="About | Signals & Systems"
  description="Learn more about JELL and the Signals & Systems publishing platform."
>
  <Nav slot="header" />
  
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <header class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">About</h1>
      </header>
      
      <section class="prose lg:prose-xl mx-auto mb-12">
        <h2>About the Platform</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Signals & Systems</strong> is a personal, self-hosted publishing platform designed for long-form, 
          markdown-native articles enriched with interactive elements. Built with the latest web technologies, 
          it emphasizes performance, accessibility, and developer experience.
        </p>
        <p>
          The platform is built with a minimalistic approach, implementing new features as needed for new articles.
          This allows for a focused, iterative development process that closely aligns with content creation.
        </p>
        <h3>Key Features</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Content-First Design</strong>: Clean typography and layout optimized for reading</li>
          <li><strong>Interactive Elements</strong>: MDX support for embedding custom React components</li>
          <li><strong>Responsive Design</strong>: Optimized for all devices from mobile to desktop</li>
          <li><strong>Performance Focused</strong>: Fast load times with minimal JavaScript</li>
          <li><strong>Series Support</strong>: Group related articles with automatic navigation</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Technology Stack</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Framework</strong>: Astro – A modern static site generator</li>
          <li><strong>Markdown Extension</strong>: MDX – For embedding components in content</li>
          <li><strong>Styling</strong>: Tailwind CSS – Utility-first CSS framework</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics</strong>: Google Tag Manager with GA4</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting</strong>: GitHub Pages with automated deployment</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>The Devlog Series</h2>
        <p>
          An important aspect of this platform is its self-documenting nature. The 
          <a href="/series/devlog">Devlog Series</a> chronicles the process of building 
          and evolving this platform, providing insights into the technical decisions, challenges faced, 
          and ethical considerations that arise in the development process.
        </p>
        <p>
          The series also explores the concept of "vibecoding" - a new approach to software development that leverages AI to automate parts of the coding process. It's characterized by focusing on the overall intent of the project and allowing AI tools to handle the syntax and structure. Essentially, developers describe what they want to achieve in natural language, and AI tools generate the code.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="mb-12 bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About the Author</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start not-prose">
          <div class="w-full md:w-1/3">
            <img 
              src="/images/author-jell.svg" 
              alt="JELL" 
              class="rounded-lg shadow-md w-full"
              loading="lazy"
              onerror="this.src='/images/author-placeholder.svg'"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="w-full md:w-2/3">
            <h3>JELL</h3>
            <p>
              JELL is an innovator, educator, and technologist exploring the confluence of AI, higher education, 
              and ethical technology. Through <em>Signals & Systems</em>, JELL shares insights, experiments, 
              and reflections on building meaningful digital experiences, and other random things.
            </p>
            <p>
              With a background spanning both educational theory and software development, JELL is interested 
              in how technology can enhance learning experiences while remaining ethical and accessible.
            </p>
            <div class="flex space-x-4">
              <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonathan-engeln/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="hover:text-blue-600">
                <span class="sr-only">LinkedIn</span>
